'''John Greer''' is a Canadian sculptor.

Greer has exhibited his work since 1967 extensively in Canada and the USA, Iceland and Korea. Greer studied Fine Art from 1962<U+2013>1967 in Halifax, Montreal and Vancouver. He taught sculpture at [[NSCAD University]] in Halifax for 26 years and is based in [[LaHave]], [[Nova Scotia]], [[Dallas, Texas]] and [[Pietrasanta]], [[Italy]]. Greer public commissions include ''Gathering, 2001'' for a park in Seoul, Korea and ''Reflection, 2001'', the [[Monument to Canadian Aid Workers]] in Ottawa, Canada. His work ''Origins, 1995'' is permanently installed in the Ondaatje courtyard of the [[Art Gallery of Nova Scotia]]. He has an exhibition in Brookhaven College, Farmers Branch Texas. The title is Alluding to Allusion and it is up from March 6 - April 11, 2008 with a reception on April 11.

